Do this to fix the registration problem:

1. navigate to C:\Documents and Settings\All Users\Application Data\element5\Licenses
(make sure you display hidden folders to see it)
2. you should see one or several files that look something like this B1FFA000.dat . delete all of them
these are screwed up license files that are no longer working due to hardware id's/mac address/and other things being 
changed on your system. The SafeCast system that ZBrush/element5 uses checks these licnese files during startup of zbrush.
3. fter you have deleted them all start up zbrush.. you should now be able to enter the normal code that you can get from the Paradox Keygen. Basiclly this just makes the protection system for ZBrush2 think you are doing a fresh install.

block ZBrush with a firewall like zonealarm
